1) Fill the file .secrets using the example from .secrets.example
2) Export this file to base64: base64 -i .secrets
3) add a variable ENCODED_SECRETS in github secrets with the value of the previous step

To run the destroy workflow:
Same steps from above, but run trigger it manually in github:
1) Go to your GitHub repo → Click on “Actions”.
2) On the left sidebar, locate “destroy.yml”.
3) Click “Run workflow” (usually a dropdown button).
4) Confirm and trigger the execution.